HEADWORD: Jumelle
<hw>Ju`melle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F., fem. of
<ets>jumeau</ets>, fr. L. <ets>gemellus</ets>. Cf. <er>Gemel</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>Twin; paired; -- said of various objects made
or formed in pairs, as a binocular opera glass, a pair of gimmal rings,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
